author: Devin Witham
text: I keep thinking it's Saturday. There must have been a glitch in the matrix because I'm not convinced it's Sunday.

author: Devin Witham
text:
Remember in Harry Potter where everyone lined up to face there fears and cast a spell to overcome it?

I looked myself in the mirror and realized the damage I've gone through and done to myself. This is the year to heal and sweat success. There's a lot that needs to be done.

author: Devin Witham
text: I no longer wanna fear not doing enough for friends or family. What I'm scared about is becoming bitter with the world for not giving me what I think I deserve when I never deserved anything at all. All the energy for resentment is wasted when so much more can come from my peace

author: Devin Witham
text: It's weird breaking from the expectation of what I give is what I should get. I want to love everyone because it makes me happy and I no longer wanna feel hurt when I don't recieve anything in return. Maybe those around me don't have the energy to give and that's okay.

author: Devin Witham
text: All the collective energy I felt today driving, Almost turned around 5 times 😬😭 Everything getting on my nerves

author: Devin Witham
text: Finding security in being single brings more peace than always looking for love in all the wrong places. Stand still once in a while and realize the serenity is always around you.

author: Devin Witham
text: The more time I spend alone, the more I find peace in it. It hurts for a while, maybe even a long time, but the idea of being forgotten is becoming easier. Kinda scary, kinda nice.
